# ESPHome Flash Command

Always flash AND show logs in the same command. Never use `--no-logs`.

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT — always use this form (device pinned to avoid interactive prompt)
cp -r "/Users/jeff/ESPHome Projects/CST Temp Module/." /tmp/cst-temp-module/ ; cd /tmp/cst-temp-module && esphome run cst-temp-module.yaml --device /dev/cu.wchusbserial5A461125811 2>&1

# ❌ WRONG — never suppress logs, never omit --device
cd /tmp/cst-temp-module && esphome run cst-temp-module.yaml --no-logs
```

- Source files live in `/Users/jeff/ESPHome Projects/CST Temp Module/`
- Always `cp -r` the source to `/tmp/cst-temp-module/` first (path has spaces, ESPHome chokes on them), then run from `/tmp/cst-temp-module/`
- Always pass `--device /dev/cu.wchusbserial5A461125811` to avoid the interactive serial-vs-OTA port prompt
- Set `block_until_ms: 0` to background the flash, then use AwaitShell with pattern matching for log output
